1
00:02:12,650 --> 00:02:14,110
H-He beat him...

2
00:02:14,660 --> 00:02:16,870
H-He beat Captain Kuro!

3
00:02:17,530 --> 00:02:21,080
Even the Marines were no match
for Kuro of a Thousand Plans!

4
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,710
But he really beat him!

5
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:24,920
Just who are you?!

6
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:27,090
Monkey D. Luffy.

7
00:02:27,540 --> 00:02:33,130
I'd never lose to a pirate who ditches
his name and runs from the sea.

8
00:02:33,130 --> 00:02:37,100
The only time a pirate should
abandon his name is when he dies!

9
00:02:37,550 --> 00:02:40,930
Luffy?! Nope, doesn't ring a bell...

10
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:44,440
Remember my name
for the rest of your lives!

11
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:47,150
I'm the man who's gonna
be King of the Pirates!

12
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,690
This guy's...

13
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:55,450
Take him and go!

14
00:02:57,070 --> 00:02:59,200
Never come back!

15
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:03,410
Run!

16
00:03:10,130 --> 00:03:12,260
You did good.

17
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:15,220
Weigh anchor! Hurry!

18
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:19,800
I guess even you would collapse
after all you've been through...

19
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,640
So...

20
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:23,890
what were you mad about earlier?

21
00:03:24,230 --> 00:03:26,480
I hate them.

22
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,350
They're wrong.

23
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:32,230
That's not how crewmates
are supposed to act.

24
00:03:32,570 --> 00:03:34,400
What're you talking about?

25
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,990
It's in their nature.

26
00:03:35,990 --> 00:03:40,030
Pirates aren't exactly the merry
bunch you make them out to be.

27
00:03:40,410 --> 00:03:41,780
I want some meat.

28
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:44,500
You're unbelievable!

29
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:55,510
Can you keep everything that's
happened here a secret?

30
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:57,180
What?! Keep it a secret?!

31
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:59,090
Why would we do that?!

32
00:03:59,090 --> 00:04:03,100
Yeah! After we just fought
for the sake of the village!

33
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,980
I bet it'll change how
everyone thinks of you!

34
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:08,480
You'll be the village hero!

35
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,350
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

36
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:13,570
Usopp, you need to clear
up this misunderstanding.

37
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:15,990
What misunderstanding?

38
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:19,490
All they did was call me
a liar, same as always.

39
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:25,120
Why go and scare everyone
when it's been settled?

40
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,580
This was a one-time thing.

41
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:34,420
No pirate's going out of their way
to attack a remote village like this one again.

42
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:38,630
I'm just going to pretend
that nothing ever happened.

43
00:04:39,130 --> 00:04:42,680
It was all a lie.

44
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:47,890
But of course, I can't force you.

45
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:49,480
No, we can do it!

46
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,150
If it's for the good of the village!

47
00:04:52,150 --> 00:04:52,900
I agree!

48
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,610
Me too! I'll never say a word, ever!

49
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:58,320
Kaya...

50
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:00,780
Will that be hard for you?

51
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:05,990
No.

52
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:12,960
Where could Usopp be this morning?

53
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:17,460
It just doesn't feel right...
I can't get motivated.

54
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:20,050
Mommy...

55
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:23,260
Is Mr. Liar not coming today?

56
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,640
That lying runt...

57
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:27,890
Why is he so late?!

58
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,850
You think maybe I was
a bit too harsh yesterday?

59
00:05:31,850 --> 00:05:35,110
I'm sure he'll be back
to his old tricks tomorrow!

60
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,730
Just watch.

61
00:05:41,530 --> 00:05:42,700
Thanks!

62
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:46,030
I wouldn't have been able to protect
the village without you guys!

63
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:48,580
What're you talking about?

64
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:51,870
If it weren't for you,
I wouldn't have done a thing!

65
00:05:52,330 --> 00:05:53,750
Me neither!

66
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:57,000
Who cares about that?

67
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,210
I made a killing!

68
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:06,180
Thanks to this incident,

69
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:08,310
I've finally made a decision.

70
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:18,730
Captain Usopp! What was it
you wanted to talk to us about?

71
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:24,110
You guys fought well against
those Black Cat Pirates!

72
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:27,700
As captain, I feel very proud!

73
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:32,790
We overcame our biggest
and greatest battle since we formed

74
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:37,420
the Usopp Pirates five years ago,
when you guys were just four years old!

75
00:06:37,420 --> 00:06:38,290
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

76
00:06:38,290 --> 00:06:39,750
So, I know this is sudden...

77
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:43,670
but I've decided to set out
to sea by myself!

78
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:49,220
I'm gonna be a real pirate!

79
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:58,860
I'd always been unsure of
whether I should stay or go...

80
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:02,570
But... when I met them,
I finally made up my mind!

81
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:07,030
I feel that as a man, I must
set out onto the vast ocean!

82
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:07,910
So...

83
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:09,990
I'm leaving this village!

84
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:15,120
The pirate flag is calling me!

85
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:20,670
What other reason do you need?!

86
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:24,170
Captain! You're lying, right?!

87
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,930
You're lying again, right?!

88
00:07:27,930 --> 00:07:29,930
It's way too sudden!

89
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:32,810
Don't you love this village, Captain?!

90
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:35,690
What'll happen to the Usopp Pirates?!

91
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:40,480
You've been good to me, guys...

92
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:43,990
I plan to leave without
telling the villagers.

93
00:07:43,990 --> 00:07:45,990
Give them my regards.

94
00:07:45,990 --> 00:07:47,240
No...

95
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,120
I don't want to!

96
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,990
Don't go, Captain!

97
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:55,960
Do you remember this place?

98
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,580
This is where we first met.

99
00:08:08,130 --> 00:08:09,180
All done!

100
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:10,890
Mr. Liar!

101
00:08:11,930 --> 00:08:14,600
Who are you guys?! Don't act
all buddy-buddy with me!

102
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,390
But you're famous!

103
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:18,310
Yeah, you're like a celebrity...

104
00:08:19,150 --> 00:08:20,230
I see!

105
00:08:20,230 --> 00:08:24,530
Finally some respect! So, people
are now calling me Captain Usopp!

106
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:27,860
Everyone calls you Usopp the Liar!

107
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:33,530
Alright! From this day forth, you're
members of the Usopp Pirates too!

108
00:08:33,910 --> 00:08:36,200
– What?
– What?

109
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:37,000
Don't "what" me!

110
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,960
A lot's happened, huh?

111
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,210
It's Cerberus!

112
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:44,880
Scare it away!

113
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,340
A dragon!

114
00:08:47,340 --> 00:08:49,880
Let's capture it!

115
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,180
Flour Star!

116
00:08:51,970 --> 00:08:53,930
You're amazing, Captain!

117
00:08:54,260 --> 00:08:55,890
But of course!

118
00:08:55,890 --> 00:08:58,680
I am a brave warrior of the sea!

119
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:02,860
We don't wanna hear
about the good old days!

120
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,980
Yeah! We don't wanna
hear about that!

121
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,980
This isn't like you, Captain!

122
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:10,070
Why are you saying this stuff now?!

123
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:13,030
It's almost like you're...

124
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:15,660
You're so stupid, Captain!

125
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:17,660
Stupid!

126
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:27,340
What are your ambitions in life?!

127
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,470
To run a pub!

128
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:33,220
To be a master carpenter!

129
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:35,390
To be a novelist!

130
00:09:36,390 --> 00:09:39,730
Then swear right here that you'll
continue on each of your paths...

131
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:45,310
and never let the fires
of your ambitions go out!

132
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,980
As of today...

133
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:52,740
the Usopp Pirates...

134
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:02,620
are disbanded!

135
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:10,300
Well, we've eaten.
We should get going now.

136
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,220
Yeah...

137
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:14,510
There you are!

138
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:15,890
Hey, miss!

139
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:17,510
You're out of bed already?

140
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:18,220
Yes...

141
00:10:19,970 --> 00:10:26,610
My illness this past year was due
to the grief from losing my parents.

142
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:30,150
Usopp's been there
to cheer me up, but...

143
00:10:30,820 --> 00:10:32,780
I can't stay coddled forever!

144
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:40,200
I've prepared a little something
for you as a token of my gratitude!

145
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,580
Please accept it!

146
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:49,670
All packed...

147
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:54,090
Guess it's farewell to this house, too!

148
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:02,730
What?!

149
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:09,060
What the...? I can't get out!

150
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:12,530
Damn it!

151
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:32,960
A caravel!

152
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:37,260
Can we really have this?!

153
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:39,220
Yes, it's all yours!

154
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:45,600
It's a slightly older model,
but I designed it myself!

155
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:52,270
A carvel-built caravel, with lateen sails
and a central stern rudder...

156
00:11:53,190 --> 00:11:56,030
the Going Merry!

157
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:58,950
Let me explain the running rigging!

158
00:11:58,950 --> 00:12:02,030
First, about the clew-garnet
yard adjustment–

159
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:03,290
No, no!

160
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:05,410
You can explain the ship stuff to me!

161
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:08,290
What a nice ship!

162
00:12:08,290 --> 00:12:11,710
Especially the front—it's so cool!

163
00:12:11,710 --> 00:12:15,840
We've loaded it with everything we thought
you might need on your voyage.

164
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,630
Thanks! It leaves
everything to be desired!

165
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:20,720
It's "nothing to be desired," you idiot.

166
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,600
Stop this thing!

167
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,890
Usopp!

168
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:30,730
What's he doing?

169
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:32,610
Let's just stop him.

170
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:34,780
He's about to collide with the ship.

171
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,860
Th-Thanks...

172
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:41,820
Yeah.

173
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:46,790
So... you're really going
out to sea, Usopp?

174
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,120
Yeah.

175
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:51,380
I figured I should get going
before I lose my nerve.

176
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,790
Don't stop me now.

177
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:55,000
I won't.

178
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,460
I could just tell somehow.

179
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:58,920
That's kind of sad, too!

180
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:01,760
The next time I come to this village,

181
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:05,350
my stories will sound more
unbelievable than any tall tale!

182
00:13:06,810 --> 00:13:09,140
Okay! I look forward to it!

183
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:11,690
You guys take care, too!

184
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,730
Let's meet again sometime!

185
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:14,520
How come?

186
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,900
Huh? "How come?"

187
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:19,280
Man, would it kill you to play nice?

188
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:23,450
I'm gonna be a pirate too, so we'll
meet on the high seas eventually!

189
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:25,580
What're you talking about?

190
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:26,450
Get on already.

191
00:13:26,450 --> 00:13:27,330
What?

192
00:13:27,330 --> 00:13:29,790
You're one of us now, aren't you?

193
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,130
I-I...

194
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,130
I get to be captain, right?!

195
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,170
Don't be dumb!

196
00:13:39,170 --> 00:13:40,760
I'm the captain!

197
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,620
There goes the captain...

198
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:05,450
Yeah.

199
00:14:05,450 --> 00:14:08,830
But he's with those guys,
so I feel less worried now.

200
00:14:08,830 --> 00:14:10,080
Yeah.

201
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:12,410
They're stronger than
anyone I've ever seen.

202
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,170
It makes sense though.

203
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:16,790
He always said he
wanted to be a pirate.

204
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:19,670
The villagers won't be happy
to hear it, though...

205
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:25,390
It's all so sudden... He's the
reason this place was so lively.

206
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:30,430
I just had an idea!

207
00:14:30,430 --> 00:14:31,930
– What is it?
– What is it?

208
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,520
Merry...

209
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,560
Yes?

210
00:14:36,310 --> 00:14:39,230
Lying is painful...

211
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:41,820
Are you referring to Klahadore?

212
00:14:41,820 --> 00:14:42,780
No...

213
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:48,080
You mean how you actually wanted
to stop Usopp from going?

214
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:52,910
Miss...

215
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:58,710
the villagers once told me
a story from his childhood.

216
00:15:00,210 --> 00:15:04,220
Shortly after Usopp's father
ran off from the village,

217
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:07,260
his mother passed away.

218
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:14,140
The pirates are coming!

219
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:15,890
The pirates are coming!

220
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:19,480
Dad's pirate ship is here!

221
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:19,480
H-Hold on, Usopp!

222
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,110
You mustn't shout!

223
00:15:22,190 --> 00:15:24,820
Dad came to pick us up!

224
00:15:25,490 --> 00:15:30,950
D-Don't be silly... Usopp...

225
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:36,420
But he said he'd take us with him
when you get better, Mom!

226
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:40,880
Your father won't be coming back...

227
00:15:41,420 --> 00:15:48,010
But... I'm proud to have married him...

228
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:50,640
There's a miracle cure out there!

229
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:52,930
It can cure any illness!

230
00:15:52,930 --> 00:15:54,770
You're so silly...

231
00:15:54,770 --> 00:15:57,020
You dream too much...

232
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:58,900
I don't care if I'm silly!

233
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:00,770
Of course I dream!

234
00:16:00,770 --> 00:16:04,990
I'm the son of a pirate!

235
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:10,700
Grow up to be a brave man
like your father...

236
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:22,000
The pirates are coming!

237
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,880
Perhaps out of loneliness,

238
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:27,510
he continued to shout it out
after she passed.

239
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:33,720
All in the hopes that his father's pirate ship
would one day be at the shore...

240
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:36,770
that one day, he would
come back for him.

241
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:46,070
The villagers say that lie of his
also contains his wish.

242
00:16:46,070 --> 00:16:49,280
Pirates!

243
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:53,200
As someone who lost his
own parents in this village,

244
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:58,000
it's no wonder he couldn't
ignore you when you lost yours.

245
00:16:58,540 --> 00:17:02,630
You will need to grow
stronger now, too!

246
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:06,880
To live up to everything
he's done until today!

247
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:09,970
Yes!

248
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:16,640
To our new ship and crewmate!

249
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:19,100
– Cheers!
– Cheers!

250
00:17:22,310 --> 00:17:27,820
They said they weren't gonna die,
that they would fight to live.

251
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:33,320
Usopp's lies always spoke
about the joy of living.

252
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:35,620
They cheered me up
and told me to live!

253
00:17:35,990 --> 00:17:37,410
Indeed.

254
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:39,580
Here we go!

255
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:41,580
Are we really gonna do this?!

256
00:17:41,580 --> 00:17:44,840
You bet! We're following
in our captain's footsteps!

257
00:17:47,800 --> 00:18:06,440
– The pirates are comiiing!
– The pirates are comiiing!

258
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:56,050
You know what, Merry?

259
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,930
I'm going to be a doctor!

260
00:18:00,390 --> 00:18:03,350
What a wonderful ambition!

